The paper deals with the performance analysis of compressed sensing reconstruction, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields of computer science. However, based on the abstract and the keywords, it is most likely that the paper belongs to the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Signal Processing (cs.SP) sub-categories, as it deals with the recovery of a sparse signal from noisy random projections. The paper also mentions numerical simulations, which suggests that it may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.MM) or Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper mentions that the result holds irrespective of whether the noise is white or correlated, which suggests that it may belong to the Statistical Learning (cs.SI) sub-category.
